Step 1. Calculate the Quick Assets.
• Cash on Hand: 2,602,624.45 
• Bank Deposits: 4,283,110.81 
• Interest Receivable: 15,023.59 
• Accounts Receivable: 2,117,339.65 
Sum of Quick Assets = 2,602,624.45 + 4,283,110.81 + 15,023.59 + 2,117,339.65 = 9,018,098.50

Step 2. Identify the Total Current Liabilities from the balance sheet.
• Total Current Liabilities = 378,850.51

Step 3. Compute the Quick Ratio.
Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities = 9,018,098.50 / 378,850.51 ≈ 23.80

Step 4. Calculate the Net Profit Margin.
• Net Profit from the income statement = 835,266.51
• Total Revenue from the income statement = 2,637,011.03
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100% = (835,266.51 / 2,637,011.03) × 100% ≈ 31.68%

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "23.80",
    "Net Profit Margin": "31.68%"
  }
}
